				"synopsis": {
					"type": 23,
					"value": "Venturing farther into what is now a goblin camp but was once a temple of Selûne (the moon goddess, rival to her own goddess, Shar), Shadowheart reacts with disgust. She notes how the crude goblin decoration is an improvement upon the surviving signs of Selûne worship. If Shadowheart isn't known to be a Shar worshipper, her comments are a little more veiled."
